                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
				<h2>Last Updated: 12:42PM 19/06/2023</h2>
				<p>This Privacy Policy ("Policy") explains how MK College Connect ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, shares, and protects personal information of the users ("you" or "your") who access or use the MK College Connect website/application ("MKCC" or "MK Connect") as an internal staff member of MK College. This Policy also outlines your rights and choices concerning your personal information.</p>

				<p>By accessing or using MKCC, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described herein. If you do not agree with any part of this Policy, please refrain from accessing or using MKCC.</p>

				<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
				<p>1.1 Personal Information</p>
				<p>We may collect personal information from you when you access or use MKCC. This information may include, but is not limited to:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Your name</li>
					<li>Contact details (email address, phone number)</li>
					<li>Job title or position</li>
					<li>Profile information</li>
					<li>Mentoring preferences and goals</li>
					<li>Communication content exchanged through MKCC</li>
					<li>Any other information you provide to us voluntarily</li>
				</ul>

				<p>1.2 Usage Data and Cookies</p>
				<p>We may also collect certain usage information automatically when you access or use MKCC. This may include:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>IP address</li>
					<li>Browser type and version</li>
					<li>Device type and unique identifiers</li>
					<li>Operating system</li>
					<li>Date and time of access</li>
					<li>Pages viewed and actions taken on MKCC</li>
					<li>Referring/exit pages</li>
					<li>Cookies and similar technologies (please see our Cookie Policy for more information)</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
				<p>2.1 Provision of Services</p>
				<p>We use the information we collect to provide and maintain MKCC, facilitate communication between mentors and mentees, and improve our services. This includes:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Facilitating mentoring relationships</li>
					<li>Notifying you about updates and improvements</li>
					<li>Responding to your inquiries and requests</li>
					<li>Administering your account and preferences</li>
					<li>Customizing MKCC based on your preferences and interests</li>
					<li>Analyzing usage trends and patterns</li>
					<li>Enforcing our Terms and Conditions</li>
				</ul>

				<p>2.2 Communication and Support</p>
				<p>We may use your personal information to communicate with you regarding MKCC, including:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Sending administrative and service-related messages</li>
					<li>Responding to your inquiries and providing support</li>
					<li>Sending newsletters, updates, and promotional materials (where permitted by law or with your consent)</li>
				</ul>

				<p>2.3 Legal Compliance</p>
				<p>We may use or disclose your personal information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or governmental requests, as well as to protect our rights, privacy, safety, and property or that of our users.</p>

				<h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
				<p>3.1 Service Providers</p>
				<p>We may share your personal information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating and maintaining MKCC. These service providers are bound by confidentiality obligations and are authorized to use your personal information only as necessary to provide services to us.</p>

				<p>3.2 Legal Requirements</p>
				<p>We may share your personal information if we believe it is necessary to:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or governmental requests</li>
					<li>Investigate potential violations of our Terms and Conditions</li>
					<li>Detect, prevent, or address security or technical issues</li>
					<li>Protect our rights, privacy, safety, and property or that of our users</li>
				</ul>

				<p>3.3 Consent</p>
				<p>We may share your personal information with your consent or as otherwise disclosed at the time of collection.</p>

				<h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
				<p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. We will securely delete or anonymize your personal information when it is no longer needed.</p>

				<h2>5. Security</h2>
				<p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

				<h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
				<p>6.1 Access and Updates</p>
				<p>You may access, review, update, or correct your personal information through your MKCC account settings. If you need further assistance, please contact us using the information provided at the end of this Policy.</p>

				<p>6.2 Opt-out</p>
				<p>You have the right to opt-out of receiving promotional communications from us. You can exercise this right by following the instructions in the communications or by contacting us.</p>

				<p>6.3 Cookies</p>
				<p>You can manage cookies and similar technologies through your browser settings. Please refer to our Cookie Policy for more information on how we use cookies and how you can control them.</p>

				<h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
				<p>MKCC is not intended for children under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from anyone under the age of 18. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided personal information to us, please contact us, and we will promptly delete such information.</p>

				<h2>8. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
				<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements, or services. We will post the revised Privacy Policy on MKCC and indicate the "Last Updated" date at the beginning of this Policy. Your continued use of MKCC after the revised Privacy Policy is effective constitutes your acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

				<h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
				<p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at:</p>
				<p>MK College Connect</p>
				<p>Email: info@mkcollegeconnect.com</p>

				<p>Thank you for using MK College Connect!</p>
